en: Rare Books and Special Collections, Hesburgh Libraries, University of Notre Dame.
A journal of sermon notes compiled by the Puritan divine Nathaniel Rogers (1598-1655), before and after his emigration from England to Massachusetts in 1636.
nathaniel rogers, sermons, notebook, preaching, new england, first congregational church
The volume contains notes for at least 19 sermons audited by Rogers, and more than 100 composed by him.
University of Notre Dame. Hesburgh Libraries, Department of Special Collections
Sermon notebook, ca. 1634-ca. 1645. Item 1 (MSN/MN 8013-1-B). 1 volume, 16 cm., 198 leaves, with 392 pages of content
